@{fg shine}@{bg fill}                                 Installing@{fg text}                                  @{bg back}


          This is a very simple task, but I will describe it step by step
          anyway.

          1. Unarchive the AB3-LCG archive (which you already have done).

          2. Put the AB3-LCG directory wherever you like.

          3. Rename the version you intend to use to AB3-LCG.

             AB3-LCG is programmed in AmosPro and can therefor either have
             the Amos.library 2.00 included or shared.
             The library is not included in this archive.
             Use AB3-LCG if you don't have Amos.library installed
             or AB3-LCG_nolib if you do have it.

          4. Doubleclick on the icon and go!


          @{" Usage " link "Usage" 0}

