@{fg shine}@{bg fill}                                   Usage@{fg text}                                     @{bg back}


          This is quite self-explaining, so I won't waste too many bytes on
          this.

          The GUI consists of two seperate fields. One for player equipment
          and one for general data.


          Player Equipment:

          Lifes: Enter the ammount of lifes for player 1 and 2 in the
                 appropriate box or use the sliders.

          Keys:  Enter the ammount of keyes for player 1 and 2 in the
                 appropriate box or use the sliders.

          Weaponry: Use the cyclegadgets to select the level of each
                    weapon for both players.


          General Data:

          Location: Use the cyclegadget to select which tower to enter.

          Level: Click a checkbox to choose towerlevel.

          Entrance: Each level can have several entrances. Click a checkbox
                    to choose entrance. The centergadget is for elevators.

          Credits: Enter the ammount of credits in the box or use the
                   slider. The maximum is 255,000 credits.


          Other gadgets:

          Print: Prints the levelcode and armoury on paper. Some extended
                 information is available.

          All to Max: Sets all values to their maximum.

          Iconify: Iconifies AB3-LCG. Click the closegadget in the
                   iconified window to uniconify.

          Quit: Guess what!!


          Other textzones:

          Levelcodes for 1-playergame and 2-playergame will be displayed
          in the lower left corner.


          @{" Info " link "Info" 0}

